    {
      "id": "l2-getting-by",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Getting by politely",
      "body": "# Useful phrases\n\nThree phrases save almost any situation:\n\n- **Excuse me.** (माफ़ कीजिए।) — to get attention or apologise\n- **How much is this?** (यह कितने का है?) — while shopping\n- **I do not understand.** (मुझे समझ नहीं आया।) — when you are lost\n\nIn English you can shorten *I do not* to *I don't* in speech. Both are correct; *do not* is a little more formal."
    },
